<DIV>PET GEAR&nbsp;- Bigger better pet gear is always welcome, but wouldn’t be necessary if the Pet benefited from the Mage’s equipment bonuses. However, I feel that the Pet’s gear and bonuses inferred from the Mage’s buffs/gear should stack. If someone takes the time to summon some gear and slap it on their pet, I think it is only fair that the two should stack. Also, it was suggested that there be summoned gear ONLY for mage pets. I think this is a bad idea; the coding for setting up a new kind of flag for mage pets would require a lot of work. But more importantly, we are Mages, you know Dominion over summoned creatures, and we should cherish and celebrate out role a "Pet Buffers" and not horde it for our selves. If a beast lord’s pet becomes more powerful than my pet because it has some really nice pet gear, well damnit it should...it was "buffed" by a mage after all!!</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>
