			As far as  SeanBoy76's idea of us being "pet buffers", consider this an heavy NO. We are not vending machines, we are not pet buffers, and under no circumstances should we EVER have any other pet surpass our own especially if it is by our doing. We should certainly not "cherish" it. Infact if Sony were to make the change that you suggest and allow other pets to use our items and thus surpass our own it would be the final stake through my heart. My 3 accounts would be cancelled and I would wait for the "next big thing." Infact I feel that pet toys being useable by others at this moment is wrong.<br><br>Mages are Damage. Say it with me. We are the shock troops of EQ. While we lack the quick punch of Wizards, the durability of Tanks or the great melee damage of Rogues we are the middleman. We sacrifice almost all defense save our pet (who pretty much gets flattened for the most part, and we sacrifice DPS when we need a hefty pet) for amazing damage. We have the best pet in the game (bar charm- but that is a completly different can of overpowered worms <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>)and we should never be expected to "buff" other pets to anywhere near our levels. I don't see Wizards buffing Druid nukes. Or at least that is the ideal equation. My job in this game is to destroy things with the combination of the second best nukes and the best pet- foregoing all defense. My job is not make others better at it than I am.
